<dl id="n36204f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36204f">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36204f"> 204(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Chase from room to room</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Spiritualism]</font> Mrs. Emma Hardinge, tells us that infuriated Irish Catholics would often break into the meetings and <mark>chase the spiritualists from room to room</mark>. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
